page.title: 07Landscape etc Stallingboro'
page.content: The landscape varies from the mainly industrial area, along the Humber Bank,to the village landscape which is a rural one of mainly agricultural nature. The land is flat mainly arable with a few hedges and trees. Two factories included in our plot are of a very functional nature with little thought given to architectural merit. They both are concerned with a chemical process and produce effluent which discharges into the river and the air. The rest of the buildings include farm buildings which vary from the original construction of brick and pantile which blend with their surroundings to modern construction of steel and asbestos cement sheeting. The remainder consist mainly of dwelling houses built of brick and tile. Most fields have dykes feeding into the river.
